      "question": "An architect is designing a circular fountain of radius $r = 6$ cm. Two tangents $PA$ and $PB$ are drawn to the circle from an external point $P$, such that the distance from the centre $O$ to point $P$ is $10$ cm. The line $OP$ intersects the circle at point $M$ and the chord $AB$ at point $N$.",
      "type": "case_study",
      "marks": 4,
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "i",
          "type": "mcq",
          "question": "What is the length of the tangent $PA$?",
          "answer": "(B)",
          "options": [
            "(A) $6$ cm",
            "(B) $8$ cm",
            "(C) $10$ cm",
            "(D) $4$ cm"
          ],
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "Since $OA \\perp PA$, $\\triangle OAP$ is a right-angled triangle.",
              "By Pythagoras theorem, $OP^2 = OA^2 + PA^2$.",
              "$10^2 = 6^2 + PA^2 \\Rightarrow 100 = 36 + PA^2 \\Rightarrow PA^2 = 64$.",
              "$PA = 8$ cm."
            ],
            "derivation": "$OP^2 = OA^2 + PA^2 \\\\ 10^2 = 6^2 + PA^2 \\\\ 100 = 36 + PA^2 \\\\ PA^2 = 64 \\\\ PA = 8$"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "ii",
          "type": "vsa",
          "question": "Find the length of the segment $ON$.",
          "answer": "$3.6$ cm",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "In $\\triangle OAP$, $AN$ is the altitude to the hypotenuse $OP$.",
              "By property of similar triangles $\\triangle ONA \\sim \\triangle OAP$.",
              "$OA^2 = ON \\times OP$.",
              "$6^2 = ON \\times 10 \\Rightarrow 36 = 10 \\times ON \\Rightarrow ON = 3.6$ cm."
            ],
            "derivation": "\\triangle ONA \\sim \\triangle OAP \\\\ \\frac{ON}{OA} = \\frac{OA}{OP} \\\\ ON = \\frac{OA^2}{OP} = \\frac{6^2}{10} = \\frac{36}{10} = 3.6"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "iii",
          "type": "vsa",
          "question": "Find the length of the chord $AB$.",
          "answer": "$9.6$ cm",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "In $\\triangle ONA$, $AN^2 = OA^2 - ON^2$.",
              "$AN^2 = 6^2 - 3.6^2 = 36 - 12.96 = 23.04$.",
              "$AN = \\sqrt{23.04} = 4.8$ cm.",
              "$AB = 2 \\times AN = 2 \\times 4.8 = 9.6$ cm."
            ],
            "derivation": "AN^2 = 6^2 - 3.6^2 \\\\ AN^2 = 36 - 12.96 = 23.04 \\\\ AN = 4.8 \\\\ AB = 2 \\times 4.8 = 9.6"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "iv",
          "type": "mcq",
          "question": "What is the length of $MN$?",
          "answer": "(A)",
          "options": [
            "(A) $2.4$ cm",
            "(B) $3.6$ cm",
            "(C) $6.4$ cm",
            "(D) $4.0$ cm"
          ],
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "$OM$ is the radius, so $OM = 6$ cm.",
              "$MN = OM - ON$.",
              "$MN = 6 - 3.6 = 2.4$ cm."
            ],
            "derivation": "MN = OM - ON \\\\ MN = 6 - 3.6 = 2.4"
          }
        }
      ],
